[294-py]
LEVEL=py
JQ = {{{
[(index(","), rindex(",")), indices(",")]
}}}
INPUT = {{{
"a,bc,def,ghij,klmno"
}}}
EXPECTED = {{{
[1,13,[1,4,8,13]]
}}}
JFTL = {{{
{"main": "$py=[min(i for i in range(len(_)) if _[i]==','), max(i for i in range(len(_)) if _[i]==','), [i for i in range(len(_)) if _[i]==',']]"}
}}}
COMMENT=index/rindex via min()/max() over a filtered range() comprehension, avoiding str.find/rfind entirely — stays at py tier.

[295-py]
LEVEL=py
JQ = {{{
[ index("aba"), rindex("aba"), indices("aba") ]
}}}
INPUT = {{{
"xababababax"
}}}
EXPECTED = {{{
[1,7,[1,3,5,7]]
}}}
JFTL = {{{
{"main": "$py=[min(i for i in range(len(_)) if _[i:i+3]=='aba'), max(i for i in range(len(_)) if _[i:i+3]=='aba'), [i for i in range(len(_)) if _[i:i+3]=='aba']]"}
}}}
COMMENT=Same min/max/range trick, using a slice comparison to find (overlapping) substring matches instead of find().

